        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: clarify maturity scorecard scoring",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe maturity scorecard rendered Coverage as a headline score beside Quality and Completeness, which made coverage look like an input to maturity scoring.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Render one headline `Maturity score` from Quality + Completeness only.\n- Keep Coverage, Quality, and Completeness visible in the scorecard metadata and surface/category tables.\n- Preserve the existing rendered coverage values while clarifying that coverage is not part of the maturity score.\n- Document the goal of keeping end-to-end coverage above 90% for mature Stable-or-better features over time.\n- Reject failed or blocked evidence unconditionally before rendering generated maturity docs.\n- Keep the single-card summary layout full-width and keep the renderer test fixture inside the core test boundary.\n\nThe workflow default/profile switch to `all` moved to #96595.\n\n## User Impact\n\nReaders now see that OpenClaw maturity is scored from quality and completeness, while coverage remains visible as supporting evidence and a long-term E2E coverage target.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/render-maturity-docs.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.full-core-support-boundary.config.ts test/extension-test-boundary.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 scripts/qa/render-maturity-docs.ts test/scripts/render-maturity-docs.test.ts`\n- `pnpm maturity:check`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n",
